article.description: — Cameron Krutwig had 20 points and 11 rebounds as Loyola of Chicago won its ninth consecutive game, topping Evansville 68-55 on Saturday.
article.headline: Krutwig lifts Loyola of Chicago over Evansville 68-55
article.linkText: Krutwig lifts Loyola of Chicago over Evansville 68-55
article.story: CHICAGO -- — Cameron Krutwig had 20 points and 11 rebounds as Loyola of Chicago won its ninth consecutive game, topping Evansville 68-55 on Saturday. Keith Clemons had 12 points for Loyola of Chicago (16-3, 11-1 Missouri Valley Conference). Noah Frederking had 15 points for the Purple Aces (8-9, 6-5). Evan Kuhlman added seven rebounds and five assists. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
